  <article class="about-body">
    <h2>The short career arc.</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>2025 – present</strong> · AV engineer, Sound Image / Clair Global, San Francisco.</li>
      <li><strong>2024 – 2026</strong> · Stock manager + internal tools developer, Suitsupply SF. Built the Daily Operations Platform from scratch.</li>
      <li><strong>2015 – 2022</strong> · A1 / OPS coordinator, Vocal Livre (São Paulo). Toured Brazil at 100–25,000-attendee scale. Latin Grammy–nominated production team for the album <em>Temporal</em> (2023).</li>
      <li><strong>2017</strong> · A2 at Rock in Rio, 80,000 attendees a day.</li>
      <li><strong>2012 – 2020</strong> · IT support and AV operations at UNASP and Colégio Adventista IABC, Brazil.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What I work on now.</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Live audio</strong> — FOH and monitor on Yamaha / DiGiCo / Avid, Dante-networked systems, Shure RF coordination.</li>
      <li><strong>Software</strong> — Node, Postgres, WebSockets, PWAs, MCP servers, the boring Linux deployment work that makes them stay up.</li>
      <li><strong>Hardware</strong> — <a href="/projects/shaddow">Shaddow</a>: 12 V automotive power and USB / CAN dock electronics in Flux.ai and KiCad.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

